on a six-year loan of 2.1 billion Egyptian pounds ($351 million)
to Emaar  Egypt ,  Al Mal  reported, citing unidentified sources.  Fifty-six percent of the funds will be used to refinance
existing debt, while the remainder will be invested in Emaarâ€™s
three real-estate projects in Egypt, the Cairo-based newspaper
